{
  "texts": [
    "A similar effort was recently carried out by [427,428], where NNs are designed to retain interpretability.",
    "This is achieved through sparse connections in combination with specialized activation functions representing candidate functions, such that they are able to capture classical forms of constitutive terms.",
    "Through the sparse connections in the network and the specialized activation functions, the NN's weights become physical parameters, yielding an interpretable model.",
    "This is best understood by consulting Fig. 7, where the strain energy density is expressed asψ = θ 1 0 e θ 0 0 I 1 + θ 1 1 ln(θ 0 1 I 1) + θ 1 2 e θ 0 2 I 2 1 +θ 1 2 ln(θ 0 2 I 2 1) + θ 1 3 e θ 0 3 I 2 + θ 1 4 ln(θ 0 4 I 2) +θ 1 5 e θ 0 5 I 2 2 + θ 1 6 ln(θ 0 6 I 2 2).",
    "(61)Fig. 7 Automated model discovery through a sparsely connected NN with specialized activation functions acting as candidate functions."
  ]
}